Nollywood actress and ‘The Johnsons’ star, Ada Ameh has revealed that she is battling mental health issues. Ameh cried out in a post on her Instagram page on Wednesday. She said the issue is gradually taking her life but she believes that she will not die and will get over it. The actress, who lost her only child in 2020, further stated that she has been sued over her inability to deliver on a job. “Everything is going to be fine, I have an issue right now and it’s taking my life. I no go die, we will get over it. ”I was given a job, I didn’t do the job because I had mental issues. Will people understand? They are slamming me with a bill, suing me. It’s okay,” she said in tears.